replies.bodyText:
The cancel signal is used when a Subscriber wants to clean up resources and it does not need data anymore. The publisher doesn't propagate a CancelledSubscriptionException to Subscribe.onError(Throwable). CancelledSubscriptionException is used internally to indicate that a stream has been cancelled via whenComplete().



      armeria/core/src/main/java/com/linecorp/armeria/common/stream/AbstractStreamMessage.java


        Lines 279 to 282
      in
      0bb591d







           if (subscription.notifyCancellation || !(cause instanceof CancelledSubscriptionException)) { 




               subscriber.onError(cause); 




           } 




           completionFuture.completeExceptionally(cause); 





So the CancelledSubscriptionException from the whenComplete() could be ignored.

